                  <p class="font_7" style="text-align:center;">
                   <span class="color_11">
                    <span style="font-weight:bold;">

                      The Haven Hope for Animals Fund is currently on hold until further notice. Thank you for your inquiry.

                 <div class="txtNew" data-min-height="597" data-packed="false" id="idskfcfr" style="top:224px;bottom:;left:320px;right:;width:654px;height:auto;position:absolute;min-height:597px;margin-left:calc((100% - 980px) * 0.5)">
                  <p class="font_8" style="font-size:17px;">
                   <span style="font-size:17px;">
                    <span class="color_11">
                     The Haven Hope for Animals Fund is a spay/neuter program that utilizes a voucher system.
                    </span>
                   </span>
                   <span style="font-size:17px;">
                    <span class="color_11">
                     We are not requesting that you charge a reduced rate. However, participants will be given a voucher which will authorize specific amounts that the fund will pay(will vary according to type, size, and gender of animal). The participants will pay the remaining amount of whatever fee you choose to charge,and will be able to choose who will provide services for them.
                    </span>
                   </span>
                  </p>
                  <p class="font_8" style="font-size:17px;">
                   <span style="font-size:17px;">
                    <span class="color_11">
                     <span class="wixGuard">
                      
                     </span>
                    </span>
                   </span>
                  </p>
                  <p class="font_8" style="font-size:17px;">
                   <span style="font-size:17px;">
                    <span class="color_11">
                     The Haven Hope for Animals Fund began on February 14, 2013.
                    </span>
                   </span>
                  </p>
                  <p class="font_8" style="font-size:17px;">
                   <br/>
                   <span style="font-size:17px;">
                    <span class="color_11">
                     A voucher system will be utilized for the spay/neuter program
                    </span>
                   </span>
                  </p>
                  <p class="font_8" style="font-size:17px;">
                   <span style="font-size:17px;">
                    <span class="color_11">
                     and will be assigned a value depending on the type and size of the animal.
                    </span>
                   </span>
                  </p>
                  <p class="font_8" style="font-size:17px;">
                   <span style="font-size:17px;">
                    <span class="color_11">
                     <span class="wixGuard">
                      
                     </span>
                    </span>
                   </span>
                  </p>
                  <p class="font_8" style="font-size:17px;">
                   <span style="font-size:17px;">
                    <span class="color_11">
                     Referrals will be accepted from veterinarians, other animal service organizations, and from pet owners.
                    </span>
                   </span>
                  </p>
                  <p class="font_8" style="font-size:17px;">
                   <span style="font-size:17px;">
                    <span class="color_11">
                     <span class="wixGuard">
                      
                     </span>
                    </span>
                   </span>
                  </p>
                  <p class="font_8" style="font-size:17px;">
                   <span style="font-size:17px;">
                    <span class="color_11">
                     A request/referral form is available on our website.
                    </span>
                   </span>
                  </p>
                  <p class="font_8" style="font-size:17px;">
                   <span style="font-size:17px;">
                    <span class="color_11">
                     Requests will be evaluated on a case by case basis by Dr. Brenda Wilbanks and Haven staff.
                    </span>
                   </span>
                  </p>
                  <p class="font_8" style="font-size:17px;">
                   <span style="font-size:17px;">
                    <span class="color_11">
                     <span class="wixGuard">
                      
                     </span>
                    </span>
                   </span>
                  </p>
                  <p class="font_8" style="font-size:17px;">
                   <span style="font-size:17px;">
                    <span class="color_11">
                     Additional features of the program will include the following:
                    </span>
                   </span>
                  </p>
                  <ul class="font_8 color_11" style="font-size:17px;">
                   <li>
                    <p class="font_8" style="font-size:17px;">
                     <span style="font-size:17px;">
                      <span class="color_11">
                       Volunteers will be sought who can transport the animals to the veterinarians for clients who may be disabled or elderly and cannot provide their own transportation and to provide ongoing aid if necessary.
                      </span>
                     </span>
                    </p>
                   </li>
                  </ul>
                  <p class="font_8" style="font-size:17px;">
                  </p>
                  <ul class="font_8 color_11" style="font-size:17px;">
                   <li>
                    <p class="font_8" style="font-size:17px;">
                     <span style="font-size:17px;">
                      <span class="color_11">
                       Teaching pet responsibility will be a very important part of the spay/neuter program. This will include the importance of yearly shots, having a secure area for pets, etc.
                      </span>
                     </span>
                    </p>
                   </li>
                  </ul>
                  <p class="font_8" style="font-size:17px;">
                  </p>
                  <ul class="font_8 color_11" style="font-size:17px;">
                   <li>
                    <p class="font_8" style="font-size:17px;">
                     <span style="font-size:17px;">
                      <span class="color_11">
                       Emergency vet care for those who need financial help has always been a part of the Havens contribution and will continue on a limited basis. This can also be accessed through the application on our website.
                      </span>
                     </span>
                    </p>
                   </li>
                  </ul>
                  <p class="font_8" style="font-size:17px;">
                   <span style="font-size:17px;">
                    <span class="color_11">
                     <span class="wixGuard">
                      
                     </span>
                    </span>
                   </span>
                  </p>

                       The Crisis Moment: WhySpaying and NeuteringCan Save Lives
                      </a>
                     </span>
                     "by Missi Davis
                    </span>
                   </span>
                  </p>

             <div class="txtNew" data-min-height="247" data-packed="false" id="idska15g" style="top:15px;bottom:;left:0;right:;width:977px;height:auto;position:absolute;min-height:247px;margin-left:calc((100% - 980px) * 0.5)">
              <p class="font_8" style="font-size:20px; text-align:center;">
               <span style="font-size:20px;">
                <span class="color_35">
                 <span style="font-weight:bold;">
                  The Haven Animal Care Shelter is a non-profit foundation, established in 1977 by Dr. Brenda and Joe Wilbanks. The Haven ACS is a no-kill, non-profit animal sanctuary and is generally home to over 100 animals,primarily dogs and cats. The Haven ACS occupies a seven-acre property near Lubbock, TX.In addition to special needs animals such as those with chronic illnesses and the elderly, The Haven ACS shelters a wide variety of adoptable dogs and cats who are in need of good, loving homes. We encourage spay and neuter of household pets, provide educational programs for schools and community groups, and offer pet therapy programs to the community.
                 </span>
                </span>
               </span>
              </p>
              <p class="font_7" style="line-height:1.8em; text-align:justify;">
              </p>
             </div>
